    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine domini nostri Iesu Christi Dei aeterni. <persName
                            key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/21">Berengarius</persName>
                        <rs key="#Emperor/king">rex</rs>. Regali satis congruit excellentiae, ut
                        petitionibus servorum Dei libenter aures accomodet et eorum effectus devote
                        tractando utiliter instituat, quatinus id agendo et eos in divinis cultibus
                        ferventiores reddat, et pro his apud Dominum devotis eorum praecibus
                        aeternam remunerationem percipiat. Omnium igitur sancte Dei Ecclesiae
                        nostrorumque praesentium scilicet ac futurorum comperiat industria, eo quod
                            <persName key="#Bishops" ref="#people/178">Azzo</persName> venerabilis
                            <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/108">sancte <placeName
                                ref="#places/191">Regiensis</placeName> ecclesiae</orgName>
                        <rs key="#Bishops">presul</rs> per <persName key="#Intercessory #Queen"
                            ref="#people/155">Berchtilam</persName> dilectam <rs
                            key="#legallyRecognisedUnionWith">coniugem</rs> et <rs key="#Queen"
                            >consortem regni</rs> nostri nostrae suggessit <rs key="#Intercessory"
                            >mansuetudini</rs>, ut quasdam res ecclesiae suae, quas quondam beatae
                        memoriae <persName key="#Bishops" ref="#people/164">Sigefredus</persName>
                        eiusdem ecclesiae <rs key="#Bishops">pontifex</rs> in <rs key="#Canons"
                            >canonicorum</rs> ibidem <orgName
                            key="#Houses #Confinia #Rivers #Casae/cassinae_massaricie #Wine #Churches #Royal_slave"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1418">Deo beateque Dei genitrici semperque
                            virgini Mariae sanctoque Michaheli Archangelo Dei</orgName> militantium
                        usibus cotidianisque vite stipendiis ad utiliorem transferens ordinem divina
                        inspiratione constituit, et postmodum tam ab eiusdem ecclesie pontificibus
                        quamque a <rs key="#Boni_viri/boni_homines">bonis hominibus</rs> Deumque
                        timentibus eidem <rs key="#Churches/religious_bodies">kanonice</rs> oblatae
                        sunt, nos pro Dei omnipotentis amore animeque nostrae omniumque parentum
                        nostrorum mercede nostra regali plenius ac firmius auctoritate
                        corroboraremus, quatinus eisdem Dei famulis largitionis nostrae fultis
                        praesidiis devotius Dei famulatum exequi et pro nobis attentius Domini
                        misericordiam exorare delectet. Nos autem tanti pontificis praecibus
                        assentientes, hos nostrae confirmationis apices fieri iussimus, per quos
                        omnino decernimus atque statuimus, ut ab hinc in futurum omnes res, quae
                        prefate kanonice oblate sunt vel oblate fuerint, perhenniter stabilite
                        permaneant. <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            >Ecclesia</rs> scilicet <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/102">Sancti Michahelis Archangeli</orgName> et
                            <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            >Sancti Peregrini</orgName>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/103">Sanctique Faustini</orgName> et <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            >Sancti Vitalis</orgName> cum <rs
                            key="#Confinia #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >omnibus pertinentiis et adiacentiis earum</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            >ecclesia</rs> quoque <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/109">Sancti Ambrosii</orgName> et <rs
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >corticella</rs> atque <rs
                            key="#Rivers #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >rivus Frigidus</rs> cum omnibus pertinentiis et adiacentiis earum, et
                            <placeName ref="#places/196">in <geogName
                                key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie">Gavassa</geogName></placeName>
                        <rs
                            key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >massaritia duo</rs>, et de parte <persName key="#Count"><name
                                ref="Erembertus">Heremberti</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Count">comitis</rs>
                        <rs
                            key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >massaritium unum</rs>, et <placeName>in <geogName
                                key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie">Faennio</geogName></placeName>
                        <rs
                            key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >massaritium unum</rs> quod rectum fuit per <persName><name
                                ref="Traseuertus">Trasevertum</name></persName> una cum ipsa familia
                        eiusque nepotibus, et omnes res ille de <persName key="#Priests"><name
                                ref="Dominicus">Dominico</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Priests">presbitero</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Houses #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >casae</rs> quoque <persName><name ref="Albericus"
                            >Alberici</name></persName> et <persName><name ref="Aloaldus"
                                >Aloaldi</name></persName> de <placeName ref="#places/234"
                            >Pinoso</placeName> cum pertinentiis suis, <rs
                            key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >massaritia</rs> quoque <persName key="#Priests"><name ref="Ermenfredus"
                                >Ermenfredi</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Priests">presbiteri</rs> atque res <persName key="#Priests"><name
                                ref="Geminianus">Geminiani</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Priests">sacerdotis</rs> quas in <placeName ref="#places/191"
                            >Regio</placeName> vel in <placeName>Sableta</placeName> habere visus
                        fuit, nec non et res quas <persName key="#Priests"><name ref="Rumoaldus"
                                >Rumoaldus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Priests">presbiter</rs> tenuit, et <rs
                            key="#Wine #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >vinea</rs> una de quodam <persName><name ref="Leovardus"
                                >Leovardo</name></persName> in <placeName>prato Pauli</placeName>,
                        seu <rs
                            key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >massaritium</rs> unum <placeName ref="#places/235">in <geogName
                                key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie">Maxentiatico</geogName></placeName>
                        cum <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Slave"
                            >famulis et famulabus</rs> in predicta kanonica deservientibus, et
                            <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/134">curticellam unam <placeName ref="#places/236">in
                                villa</placeName>
                        </geogName>quam <persName key="#Bishops" ref="#people/176"
                            >Rodfredus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Bishops">episcopus</rs> eisdem kanonicis habere concessit cum <rs
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >domo coltile</rs> et <rs
                            key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >massaritiis ad eam pertinentibus</rs>, seu et <rs
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Churches"
                            >ecclesiam</rs>
                        <orgName ref="#juridical_persons/110">Sancti Laurentii</orgName> quam iam
                        fatus Azzo venerabilis episcopus predictis kanonicis concessit cum omnibus
                        pertinentiis et adiacentiis suis in integrum. Insuper et <geogName
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/133">corticellam <placeName ref="#places/240"
                                >Perinianum</placeName>
                        </geogName>quam praenominatus Azzo presul <rs
                            key="#Curtes #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Inflow #Purchase"
                            >de proprio praetio comparavit</rs> et ipsis <rs key="#Canons"
                            >kanonicis</rs> ad cotidianum victum habere disposuit. Haec omnia sepe
                        nominati teneant kanonici cum <rs
                            key="#Rivers #Curtes #Massae #Fiscal_property #Outflow #Iure_proprietatis/pleno_iure #Allocation_to_churches #Other_clerics #Slave"
                            >plenissima integritate atque potestative</rs> possideant, et cuncta
                        quaecumque praeteritis aut futuris temporibus in eadem kanonica a benignis
                        largitoribus aucta fuerint per hanc nostram institutionem et confirmationem
                        ac inviolabilem corroborationem stabilita et fixa permaneant, ut <rs>nullus
                            eiusdem sedis praesul vel aliqua rei publice nostrae potestas ullo
                            umquam in tempore de praefata canonica rebusque ad eam pertinentibus
                            alienationem, commutationem, aut praecariam, aut libellariam, aut
                            emphitheosin, aut aliquam firmitatem alicui absque eorundem canonicorum
                            voluntate ac libera petitione facere presumat</rs>. Quod si quis umquam
                        ullo in tempore praelibate sedis episcopus contra hanc nostram
                        confirmationem insurgere temptaverit, aut aliquam violentiam pretaxatis
                        kanonicis facere quesierit, noverit se compositutum <rs key="#Penalty"
                            >quingentas libras auri obrizi</rs>, <rs key="#Camera_regis">medietatem
                            palatio nostro</rs> et <rs key="#Camera_of_other_public_authorities"
                            >medietatem ipsi kanonice</rs> et in eadem militantibus. Et ut haec
                        nostrae confirmationis auctoritas ab omnibus verius credatur diligentiusque
                        observetur, manu propria subter eam confirmavimus et anuli nostri
                        impressione insigniri iussimus. Signum domni Berengarii serenissimi regis.
                            <persName key="#Chancellor"><name ref="Petrus">Petrus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Chancellor">cancellarius</rs> iussu regio recognovi et subsripsi.
                        Dat. VIII id. novembr. Anno incarnationis Domini DCCCXCVIII, anno vero regni
                        domni Berengarii Gloriosissimi regis XI, indictione I. Actum <placeName
                            ref="#places/65">Papie</placeName> palatio regio. In Dei nomine
                        feliciter, amen.</ab>
                </div>
            </div>
